Rattrap glares at Dinobot. 

" Okay, so bad stuff happened a long time ago!=
  I admit I messed up!  But for the sake of Primus, can we put this behind =
us and just move on!?  Tucson's out there with Optimus Primal, Cheetor, Rod=
imus and now Nightlight!  Every astrosecond we waste here is one less we ha=
ve ta find them and get 'em back safely!  And you got Cyclonus'n Scourge ta=
 worry about too!  So let's try and work together here and actually accompl=
ish something!"

Straight Shot nods.

" Look, Dinobot, he's right, our comr=
ades need us more than ever and we really can't afford ta let them down.  M=
agmatron is out there and unless we put our differences aside, like Tucson =
was attempting to achieve with all of us, we might as well hand the planet =
over to that monster and head for the hills.  None of us want that, we work=
 too hard to defend what little territory we have.  Let's keep it that way.=
 "

She stands up on Quickstride's rump, on her hind legs.

" Tucson starte=
d this because he believes that unity is our best weapon against a formidab=
le foe such as Magmatron.  If we fought separately, none of us would surviv=
e his onslaught.  He did this for ALL of us.  He didn't have to but he did,=
 and it would be a real slap in the face for him if we let it fall apart no=
w.  Please, we gotta try ta work together, because if we don't, we could en=
d up being the losers."

Perpetually on the move and constantly busy.
